==English==

===Etymology===
From {{prefix|en|under|shorts}}, by analogy with {{m|en|underpants}}, etc.

===Noun===
{{en-plural noun}}

# {{lb|en|dated}} [[underpants|Underpants]], type of [[underwear]] worn in skin contact with the [[hip]] portion of the body, small enough to be worn invisibly under shorts. Typically refers to male, not female, underpants.
#:''I have one clean pair of '''undershorts'''.''
#: ''I have to buy more '''undershorts'''.''
#*'''1934''', {{w|Edgar Rice Burroughs}}, ''{{w|Pirates of Venus}}'', Chapter 3, p.{{nbsp}}41,<sup>[https://www.fadedpage.com/books/20170822/html.php]</sup>
#*: It being very warm, I removed all of my clothing except my '''undershorts''' and lay down to sleep.
#* '''1969''', {{w|Philip Roth}}, ''{{w|Portnoy's Complaint|Portnoy’s Complaint}}'', New York: Vintage, 1994, “The Jewish Blues,” p.{{nbsp}}47,<sup>[https://archive.org/details/portnoyscomplain00roth_0]</sup>
#*: {{...}} like a mouse [I] hop frantically about on my toes, trying to clear my feet of my '''undershorts''' before anybody can peek inside, where, to my chagrin, to my bafflement, to my mortification, I always discover in the bottommost seam a pale and wispy brushstroke of my shit.
#* '''1989''', {{w|Shashi Tharoor}}, ''{{w|The Great Indian Novel}}'', New York: Arcade, 1993, “The Thirteenth Book: Passages through India,” p.{{nbsp}}268,<sup>[https://books.google.ca/books?id=tyNahb9XtQsC&printsec=frontcover#v=onepage&q&f=false]</sup>
